slap /slæp/

(slapping,slapped,slaps) 

1. V-T If you slap someone, you hit them with the palm of your hand. 掴; (用手掌) 拍打 

例： He would push or slap her once in a while. 他时不时地推搡她，或是打她耳光。 

例： I slapped him hard across the face. 我重重地打了他一记耳光。 

2. N-COUNT Slap is also a noun. 掴; 拍打 

例： He reached forward and gave her a slap. 他走上前去，给了她一个耳光。 

3. V-T If you slap something onto a surface, you put it there quickly, roughly, or carelessly. 重重放下; 摔; 掼 

例： He emptied his drink and slapped the money on the bar. 他喝光了饮料，然后把钱摔在吧台上。 

4. V-T If journalists say that the authorities slap something such as a tax or a ban on something, they think it is unreasonable or put on without careful thought. (无理地或者盲目地) 强加 [非正式] 

例： The government slapped a ban on the export of unprocessed logs. 政府强制禁止出口未加工过的木料。

